@Pern_Seasons
$ #Seasons on Pern#
  A formal calendar division of Turn
to four approximately equal periods is used on Pern.

  In the Northern Hemisphere the following dates are fixed:
 ⋅ ¦01-01 — Winter Solstice;
 ⋅ ¦04-01 — Spring Equinox;
 ⋅ ¦07-01 — Summer Solstice;
 ⋅ ¦10-01 — Autumn Equinox.

  The seasons follow these dates, e.g.:
 ⋅ ¦Winter — from 01-01 until 03-30;
 ⋅ ¦Spring — from 04-01 until 06-30;
 ⋅ ¦Summer — from 07-01 until 09-30;
 ⋅ ¦Autumn — from 10-01 until 12-31/32.

